cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.PL 

The paper discusses Android app security and detection techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The focus on inter-app communication threats and collusion among multiple apps suggests a software engineering (cs.SE) aspect to the paper. The use of behavior-based analysis techniques and the comparison of tools for analysis suggests a systems and information science (cs.SI) aspect. The discussion of Android vulnerabilities and attacks may also fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and programming languages (cs.PL).
